Fix AOT IL2026/IL3050 warnings in `/tmp/sv-01d0942d296f430a8fb49cf7bc2b74c2/before/Extensions/ArmClientBuilderExtensions.cs`.

The method `AddArmClient<TBuilder, TConfiguration>` calls `RegisterClientFactory` which has `[RequiresUnreferencedCode]` and `[RequiresDynamicCode]`. The fix is to propagate these attributes to the calling method.

Use the `edit` tool to make these changes:

1. The file already has `using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;` (line 4).

2. Add `[RequiresUnreferencedCode]` and `[RequiresDynamicCode]` attributes to the `AddArmClient<TBuilder, TConfiguration>` method (the second overload, around line 27).

Change:
```csharp
        /// <summary>
        /// Registers an <see cref="ArmClient"/> instance with connection options loaded from the provided <paramref name="configuration"/> instance.
        /// </summary>
        public static IAzureClientBuilder<ArmClient, ArmClientOptions> AddArmClient<TBuilder, TConfiguration>(this TBuilder builder, TConfiguration configuration)
            where TBuilder : IAzureClientFactoryBuilderWithConfiguration<TConfiguration>
```

to:

```csharp
        /// <summary>
